### DMS-1011 — Map FK Violations to Delete Conflict Responses
#
# Manual walkthrough of the 4 FK-violation DELETE scenarios the ticket covers
# (from src/dms/tests/.../Features/References/DeleteReferenceValidation.feature).
#
# Prereqs:
#   /e2e start --relational          # dedicated edfi schema in edfi_datamanagementservice_relational
#   /e2e status                      # confirm dms-local-dms-1 is healthy
#
# End-to-end self-contained: section 1 mints the Config-Service + DMS tokens so no manual
# token paste is needed. Execute from top to bottom with the VS Code REST Client extension.

@dmsPort=8080
@configPort=8081
@dataApi=http://localhost:{{dmsPort}}/data

@sysAdminId=DmsConfigurationService
@sysAdminSecret=ValidClientSecret1234567890!Abcd

# Relational DB + password match eng/docker-compose/.env.e2e.relational.
@relationalDbName=edfi_datamanagementservice_relational
@postgresPassword=abcdefgh1!

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Bootstrap — Configuration Service token, vendor, DMS instance, application, DMS token
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1.1 Configuration-Service token
# @name configTokenRequest
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{sysAdminId}}
&client_secret={{sysAdminSecret}}
&grant_type=client_credentials
&scope=edfi_admin_api/full_access

###
@configToken={{configTokenRequest.response.body.access_token}}

### 1.2 Create a vendor scoped to the ed-fi namespace
# @name createVendor
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/vendors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "company": "DMS-1011 Demo Vendor {{$randomInt 0 9999999}}",
    "contactName": "Relational Backend",
    "contactEmailAddress": "demo@example.com",
    "namespacePrefixes": "uri://ed-fi.org"
}

###
@vendorId={{createVendor.response.body.id}}

### 1.3 Create a DMS instance pointing at the RELATIONAL database
# The connection string MUST target the dedicated relational database provisioned by
# provision-relational-e2e-database.ps1 — NOT the default edfi_datamanagementservice.
# @name createDmsInstance
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/dmsInstances
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "instanceType": "Test",
    "instanceName": "DMS-1011 Relational Instance",
    "connectionString": "host=dms-postgresql;port=5432;username=postgres;password={{postgresPassword}};database={{relationalDbName}};"
}

###
@dmsInstanceId={{createDmsInstance.response.body.id}}

### 1.4 Create an application with the NoFurtherAuthorizationRequired claim set
# (matches what the E2E relational-backend runs use — avoids namespace-authz noise while
# demoing the 409 contract)
# @name createApplication
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/applications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "vendorId": {{vendorId}},
    "applicationName": "DMS-1011 Relational Demo",
    "claimSetName": "E2E-NoFurtherAuthRequiredClaimSet",
    "educationOrganizationIds": [ 255, 255901 ],
    "dmsInstanceIds": [ {{dmsInstanceId}} ]
}

###
@clientId={{createApplication.response.body.key}}
@clientSecret={{createApplication.response.body.secret}}

### 1.5 Reload claim sets so the NoFurtherAuthRequired set is visible to DMS
POST http://localhost:{{dmsPort}}/management/reload-claimsets

### 1.6 Exchange the client credentials for a DMS bearer token
# Use HTTP Basic auth (not form-body) because the generated client_secret can contain
# characters that are significant in application/x-www-form-urlencoded — notably '&',
# which would be interpreted as a field separator and truncate the secret server-side,
# causing the DMS /oauth/token endpoint to reject the request with "Malformed Authorization
# header". The REST Client extension base64-encodes the `basic <id>:<secret>` value as a
# whole, so characters inside the secret do not need additional escaping.
# @name dmsTokenRequest
POST http://localhost:{{dmsPort}}/oauth/token
Authorization: basic {{clientId}}:{{clientSecret}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials

###
@dmsToken={{dmsTokenRequest.response.body.access_token}}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. Seed baseline descriptors + School (reused across scenarios)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2.1 GradeLevelDescriptor — First grade
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/gradeLevelDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/GradeLevelDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "First grade",
    "shortDescription": "First grade"
}

### 2.2 EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor — school
# @name edOrgCategoryDescriptor
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "school",
    "shortDescription": "school"
}

###
@edOrgCategoryDescriptorId={{edOrgCategoryDescriptor.response.body.id}}

### 2.3 CalendarTypeDescriptor — Student Specific (scenario 01)
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendarTypeDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarTypeDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "Student Specific",
    "shortDescription": "Student Specific"
}

### 2.4 LocalEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor — School (scenario 04)
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/localEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/LocalEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "School",
    "shortDescription": "School"
}

### 2.5 School 255901107 — used by scenarios 01 (Calendar target) and 02 (pre-existing reference)
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schools
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "schoolId": 255901107,
    "nameOfInstitution": "Grand Bend Elementary School",
    "educationOrganizationCategories": [
        { "educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor#school" }
    ],
    "gradeLevels": [
        { "gradeLevelDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/GradeLevelDescriptor#First grade" }
    ]
}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Scenarios — each ends in a DELETE that must return 409 with the specific
#    referencing resource name in the detail.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3.1 Scenario 01 — SchoolYearType referenced by Calendar
# Expect: 409, detail "...referenced by existing Calendar item(s)."
# @name schoolYear2022
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schoolYearTypes
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "schoolYear": 2022,
    "currentSchoolYear": false,
    "schoolYearDescription": "2021-2022"
}

###
@schoolYear2022Id={{schoolYear2022.response.body.id}}

### POST Calendar referencing School 255901107 + SchoolYearType 2022
# @name calendar2010605675
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendars
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "calendarCode": "2010605675",
    "schoolReference": { "schoolId": 255901107 },
    "schoolYearTypeReference": { "schoolYear": 2022 },
    "calendarTypeDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarTypeDescriptor#Student Specific"
}

###
@calendar2010605675Id={{calendar2010605675.response.body.id}}

### DELETE the referenced SchoolYearType — expect 409 referencing "Calendar"
DELETE {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schoolYearTypes/{{schoolYear2022Id}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### 3.2 Scenario 02 — EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor referenced by School
# The School in 2.5 already references this descriptor.
# Expect: 409, detail "...referenced by existing School item(s)."
DELETE {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptors/{{edOrgCategoryDescriptorId}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### 3.3 Scenario 03 — Student referenced by StudentEducationOrganizationAssociation
# Expect: 409, detail "...referenced by existing StudentEducationOrganizationAssociation item(s)."
# @name student604824
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/students
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "studentUniqueId": "604824",
    "birthDate": "2010-01-13",
    "firstName": "Traci",
    "lastSurname": "Mathews"
}

###
@student604824Id={{student604824.response.body.id}}

### POST the association
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/studentEducationOrganizationAssociations
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "educationOrganizationReference": { "educationOrganizationId": 255901107 },
    "studentReference": { "studentUniqueId": "604824" }
}

### DELETE the referenced Student — expect 409 referencing "StudentEducationOrganizationAssociation"
DELETE {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/students/{{student604824Id}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### 3.4 Scenario 04 — LocalEducationAgency referenced by School
# Expect: 409, detail "...referenced by existing School item(s)."
# @name lea333
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/localEducationAgencies
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "localEducationAgencyId": 333,
    "nameOfInstitution": "Grand Bend Delete",
    "localEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/LocalEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor#School",
    "categories": [
        { "educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor#school" }
    ]
}

###
@lea333Id={{lea333.response.body.id}}

### POST a second School that references the LEA
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schools
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "schoolId": 255901108,
    "nameOfInstitution": "Grand Bend Elementary School (LEA ref)",
    "educationOrganizationCategories": [
        { "educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor#school" }
    ],
    "gradeLevels": [
        { "gradeLevelDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/GradeLevelDescriptor#First grade" }
    ],
    "localEducationAgencyReference": { "localEducationAgencyId": 333 }
}

### DELETE the referenced LEA — expect 409 referencing "School"
DELETE {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/localEducationAgencies/{{lea333Id}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. Happy path — remove the blocker, retry the delete
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Closes the loop: the same SchoolYearType 2022 that returned 409 in scenario 01
# now succeeds once its referencing Calendar is gone. Proves the 409 is reversible
# (i.e. it really is a temporary dependent-item conflict, not a permanent rejection).

### 4.1 DELETE the referencing Calendar first — expect 204
DELETE {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendars/{{calendar2010605675Id}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### 4.2 Retry DELETE on the SchoolYearType — now expect 204
DELETE {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schoolYearTypes/{{schoolYear2022Id}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
